sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K2113010
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: RNA thermometer and AMP with glycine
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This construct consists of RNA thermometer (BBa_K115001) for temperature regulated system under the control of a strong promoter (BBa_J23119).It is then followed by antimicrobial peptides with glycine (BBa_K2113005),Cj blue being used as a reporter protein (BBa_K592011).Double terminator(BBa_K823017)is used to terminate the transcription.This construct could be used to study the effect of antimicrobial peptides regulated by temperature sensitive system activated above 42 degree celcius.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: SVCE_CHENNAI

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_B0034
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes:
Varies from -6 to +1 region from original sequence to accomodate BioBricks suffix.

No secondary structures are formed in the given RBS region. Users should check for secondary structures induced in the RBS by upstream and downstream elements in the +50 to -50 region, as such structures will greatly affect the strength of the RBS. Contact info for this part: Brian Chow
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Vinay S Mahajan, Voichita D. Marinescu, Brian Chow, Alexander D Wissner-Gross and Peter Carr IAP, 2003.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K115001
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: This sequence is taken from the Bradirhizobium Japonicum (BA000040.) as the 5'UTR (ROSE) of a heat shock protein (prfA).
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This part is designed as a temperature inducible RBS. Only designed so far.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: The secondary structure is important to the function of these regions, but part of the wt secondary structure is destroyed by the scar. We've tried to alter the sequence so the predicted structure (through mfold and those kind of servers) is sort of conserved, but temperature sensitivity still has to be tested. If it doesn't work, possible solution might be the addition of a larger conserved part of the wt, which implies a small part of wt protein sequence as well.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: O.M.J.A. Stassen

sbol:SequenceAnnotation.dcterms:title: Predicted Stem Loop extending to startcodon

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K2113005
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This part contains the anti-microbial peptides (AMP) with consecutive sequences of arginine and tryptophan.These peptides have antimicrobial activity against wide range of microbes. In order to increase the shelf life and stability of the peptide glycine residues are added at the N terminal.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: SVCE_CHENNAI

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: cjBlue
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This chromoprotein, cjBlue, naturally exhibits strong green/blue color when expressed. Compared to amilCP(BBa_K592009) and amilGFP(BBa_K592010), the color development is slower. On agar plates and in liquid culture, the color is readily visible to naked eye after 24-48 hours of incubation. The DNA was codon-optimized for expression in E.coli and synthesized by the Korean company Bioneer Corporation.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: Codon-optimization for expression in E.coli necessary.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Antonio Ascue Avalos

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K823017
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This is a copy of the [[Part:B0014|Part:B0014]]. Only here the part is cloned in the standard vector pSB1C3 instead of the pSB1AK3.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: This is a copy of the [[Part:B0014|Part:B0014]]. Only here the part is cloned in the standard vector pSB1C3 instead of the pSB1AK3.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_B0014
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Double terminator consisting of BBa_B0012 and BBa_B0011
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Reshma Shetty

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_B0011
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: Derived from luxICDABEG operon terminator of Vibrio fischeri <genbank>AF170104</genbank>.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Bidirectional transcriptional terminator consisting of a 22 bp stem-loop.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: In the naturally-occuring sequence there is a mismatch in the stem of the stem loop. This can be corrected via an A->G mutation (at position 40 -- sequence coordinate/not MFOLD coordinate). The above sequence does not reflect this mutation (but the MFOLD image does). This terminator's location cannot be found using some inverted repeat detectors like PALINDROME because it is too short and contains a mismatch. This one was found with the help of Tom Knight. It lies between two coding regions that point towards eachother.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Reshma Shetty

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_B0012
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: Derived from the TE terminator of T7 bacteriophage between Genes 1.3 and 1.4 <genbank>V01146</genbank>.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Transcription terminator for the E.coli RNA polymerase.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes:
Suggested by Sri Kosuri and Drew Endy as a high efficiency terminator. The 5' end cutoff was placed immediately after the TAA stop codon and the 3' end cutoff was placed just prior to the RBS of Gene 1.4 (before AAGGAG).

Use anywhere transcription should be stopped when the gene of interest is upstream of this terminator.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Reshma Shetty
